The paper introduces a regularization technique for the Dynamic Boltzmann Machine (DyBM) to improve its unsupervised learning of temporal sequences. The DyBM is a type of neural network that models time-series data, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses the moving MNIST dataset, which involves image sequences, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's focus on the biologically motivated structure of the DyBM suggests relevance to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
